<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Damian Santiago</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Would you think making a Troll shaman is actually a bad idea? I mean I know they level slowly, but its the same speed as Iksars.  I dont like iksars at all and really dont even want to think about how bad their faction is.  At least with a troll I can bank in Neriak until I kill enough DF orcs to raise FP faction.  I was just wondering if maybe there are some troll shamans out there that think it is worth the XP loss for the regen and str and stuff.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Abrax Spiritwalker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My shaman is a barbarian.  I like not having to work on faction and the wisdom was decent.  <P>I could see the advantage of playing an ogre just because they're so damn tough.  <P>Thought it was just plain stupid to play a troll.  You get low wisdom, not as tough as an ogre, all the bad faction, plus a huge xp penalty?  For that you get to heal a little faster when we've already got heal spells anyway?  No thanks.<P>Then I grouped with a 50th lvl iksar shaman.  That little lizard was putting out spells like there was no tomorrow.  With chloro plus his natural regen he was canning back mana at an unreal rate.  He's standing, he's sitting, he's canning, he's buffing, he's rooting, he's healing - I couldn't keep up with the guy.  His downtime was a fraction of mine.  <P>Never again will I say a troll or lizard are second rate shamans.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lunasicc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Regeneration cannot be beat.<P>Iscaar and Trolls have an Exp penalty because of it.<BR>They are in my opinion supperior.<P>6hp a tick at level 20 I belive.<P>p.s. attributes mean nothing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Damian Santiago</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Iksars... why would someone do that to themselves, They cant even wear their own quest armor.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sponng</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">perhaps they actually play the game for fun or for ROLE playing instead of powergaming or "to win"?<P>As a troll shaman who is regularly requested to enter into groups and with one of the lowest wisdumb's around  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  I can attest that if you play your spells right, attributes are not as much of an issue as timing and tactics.  <P>attributes do make a difference in soloing when you don't have as much mana for DD or healing, though.<P><P>------------------<BR>GuildMama Kzazua (Mama K to you!) - Xegony - Dark Legion</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dotty</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When my regeneration increased to 12 points per tick sitting, I realized I was playing the most powerful shaman race in the game. Yes, trolls have it slightly rougher getting to a high level but when they are there, they rock.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Blaz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Me havin lots of fun and me Troll Shaman. Sure it hard tu get tu high level but it pays off.<P>Just yesterday was group in Dreadlands near Kranor castle. Tank was pullin non stop all sort of tings. Since me was slowing mob, de cleric was gettin bored. He started tu stun so dam was even lower on de tanks.<P>So even at 45th got half a bubb in 2.5 hours.<P><BR>Blaz - Troll Shaman<BR>Tunare Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lunasicc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">IF your on a pvp server id say pick somthing with regeneration, but on a blue server just pick which ever one you like best.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blakkon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A natural regenniong shaman would be very nice indeed.  I chose a barbarian for two reasons though:<P>1) had just played my ranger to 47 and NEVER, i mean NEVER again will i play a  character with an exp penalty from the bottom up.<P>2) my RL wife plays a Wood elf druid and she wouldnt marry me in game if i didnt at least look human  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cidd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't think the XP penalty for the big races applies to the shaman and warriors.  I have played a barb/shaman up to 30, and have started a troll/shaman cause I wanted to be a troll, despite the worse stats, and I haven't seen any penalty yet.  I'm only level 6 but I'll see how long it takes to get to 50, since it took my wizard about 23 days of playing time, I'll compare it to that.  Also my brother played a troll/warrior up to 32 and he was always getting good xp, so I think the exp penalty only applies to the shadow knights(and boy is it a big one).<P>About troll/shamans, they are low wisdom but it can be increased to a decent number.  But you'll be getting mana back fast with cannibalize with natural and spell regen.  Not that I care about being the best, but I expect great results when I hit 24.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cattibree</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I got my Troll shaman up to 25 now and I haven't noticed any penalty because the Troll shaman is the same as a human monk is xp wise. So for me it's been kewl. I made 25 in like 3 days played time and the xp bar moves very well. <P>The regen on those buggers kicks arse with Cann and regen on.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zibzab</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would not play anything other then a Troll or Iksar Shaman . The HP Regen really helps your mana recovery when used with Canabalize/Chloro etc. And Since I couldnt stand joing the newbie-thon in Field of Bone...... Enter Zibby!<P>Zibzab Bludd<BR>34 Troll Sham/Vallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Damian Santiago</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks, I think I will Keep little Timmiy then, just wanted to make the right choice hehe.  And I do play the game for fun and not just powerleveling or I wouldnt be a troll... And half the fun is looking good while you do it.. and iksars are terrible at that hehe unless they a necro, gosh they look evil in those robes.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Baldaen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pshh<P>I'm with Damien, I saw a Iksar Necro in Black Burrow the other day I was doing /shout IKSAR IKSaR IKSAR for like twenty minute cuz I thought it was a NPC out to kill us all!!! No, but it did look wicked in that black robe with those squinched eyes, and :shivers.<P>whatever, cathca's later,</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blaz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well if you want to put numbers on Exp I got some. Taken from :<BR> <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/orderoftheblackdagger/EQexp2/" TARGET=_blank>http://www.geocities.com/orderoftheblackdagger/EQexp2/</A> <P><BR>Race:<BR>Troll have a modifier of      120<BR>Iksar have a modifier of      120<BR>Ogre have  a modifier of      115<BR>Barbarian have a modifier of  105<BR>Halfling have a modifier of    95<BR>All other have modifier of    100<P>Class:<BR>Warrior have a modifier of     09<BR>Rogue have a modifier of       09.05<BR>Healer have a modifier of      10<BR>Casting have a modifier of     11<BR>Hybrid have a modifier of      14<P>So do the math and you'll find that there is a big difference between a Barbarian Shaman and a Troll Shaman. But the regeneration on Trolls/Iksars can't be ignored. Now the question becomes "Is the regeneration worth 14.3% more Exp?"<P><BR>Blaz</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Slurm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is regeneration worth the extra exp? <P>(note: I still don't trust the percentages...  Unless one of the programers verifies it, the tests are not conclusive.)<P>YES! It is worth the extra exp.  I am an Iksar shaman, 30th level.  With the 29th level regeneration spell, and my natural regeneration, I can regen a bubble of health in 5-6 pulses (sitting).  In combat, I frequently SEE my health going up even while the mob is beating on me -if they make a weak hit.<P>So, yeah... it is worth it.  Faction is the only real deciding factor.  If you are up to dealing with faction problems, go for it.  If you want to be welcome everywhere, go barbarian.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
